The paper discusses privacy and data protection in the context of big data analysis, which is a common topic in the computer security (cs.CR) sub-category. The paper also discusses different data protection and privacy-preserving techniques, which are commonly studied in the database (cs.DB) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses legal regulations, which are commonly studied in the cyber law (cs.CY) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents case studies dealing with sensitive data, which can be related to information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
